WEBVTT

00:04.766 --> 00:05.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.766 --> 00:06.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.766 --> 00:08.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.766 --> 00:09.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: We should hammer
this out, and get it done.

00:09.966 --> 00:12.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF:
Changing his tune.

00:12.066 --> 00:16.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The president calls
on Republicans not to
leave Washington until
a health care plan

00:16.333 --> 00:18.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is approved.

00:18.300 --> 00:22.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We talk with two senators,
Roberts of Kansas and Wicker
of Mississippi, about where the

00:23.866 --> 00:26.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
effort to repeal
Obamacare stands.

00:26.000 --> 00:30.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Then: New revelations of
an undisclosed meeting
between President Trump
and Russia's President

00:32.733 --> 00:37.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Putin at the G20 summit bring
the two leaders' relationship
back into the spotlight.

00:39.066 --> 00:43.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Plus: With food stamps on the
president's chopping block,
we travel south to see what

00:45.166 --> 00:48.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
these changes could mean for
a state that overwhelmingly
supported him in the election.

00:50.866 --> 00:53.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES JACKSON, Receives SNAP
Assistance: Give me a chance to
get off the very program that

00:53.333 --> 00:55.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you're trying to cut.

00:55.966 --> 00:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I want to get off.

00:57.433 --> 01:01.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But if you take away my ability
to get off, what can I do?

01:01.500 --> 01:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:09.133 --> 01:11.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:11.966 --> 01:16.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senate
Republicans are trying
again to see if there
is a way forward on

01:21.100 --> 01:23.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
health care reform.

01:23.133 --> 01:27.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their latest bill to replace
Obamacare collapsed yesterday,
but party leaders say it may not

01:29.233 --> 01:33.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be dead yet, after a repeal-only
option also ran into opposition.

01:34.900 --> 01:37.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
President Trump called the
caucus to the White House today.

01:37.166 --> 01:42.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said he is now ready
to act, and insisted that
inaction is not an option.

01:42.066 --> 01:46.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: Frankly, I don't
think we should leave town

01:46.566 --> 01:51.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
unless we have a health
insurance plan, unless
we can give our people
great health care,

01:53.333 --> 01:54.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
because we're close.

01:54.400 --> 01:56.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're very close.

01:56.433 --> 02:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Any senator who votes against
starting debate is really
telling America that you're fine

02:03.100 --> 02:05.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with Obamacare.

02:05.200 --> 02:08.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Afterward,
Senate Majority Leader Mitch
McConnell said he still aims

02:08.866 --> 02:12.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to hold a vote next week,
but it's not clear on what.

02:12.333 --> 02:14.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:14.300 --> 02:17.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: I think we all agree
it's better to both repeal

02:17.166 --> 02:19.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and replace.

02:19.933 --> 02:23.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But we could have
a vote on either.

02:23.200 --> 02:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if we end up voting on
repeal only, it will be fully
amendable on the Senate floor.

02:30.366 --> 02:35.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if it were to pass without
any amendment at all, there's
a two-year delay before it

02:35.133 --> 02:37.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
kicks in.

02:37.700 --> 02:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will be
talking to two Republican
senators about the
state of play on health

02:40.400 --> 02:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
care reform after
the news summary.

02:43.233 --> 02:48.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Separately, there's word
that President Trump is
ending a CIA program to
arm and train moderate

02:49.500 --> 02:51.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
rebels in Syria.

02:51.633 --> 02:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The goal was to fight the regime
of President Bashar al-Assad,
but it had only limited effects

02:57.200 --> 03:00.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
after Russia intervened
to aid Assad.

03:00.133 --> 03:04.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Washington Post reports
the president made the decision
nearly a month ago, before

03:04.800 --> 03:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he met with Russian's President
Putin at the G20 summit.

03:07.433 --> 03:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Afterward, the U.S. and
Russia announced a limited
cease-fire in Syria.

03:14.366 --> 03:18.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Post account says that
the aid decision is part of a
strategy to negotiate more such

03:19.133 --> 03:21.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
deals.

03:21.100 --> 03:25.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Iran today stepped up its
defiant response to the latest
round of U.S. sanctions.

03:27.266 --> 03:30.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They target 18 individuals and
companies assisting the Iranian
ballistic missile program.

03:32.733 --> 03:37.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Tehran, President Hassan
Rouhani charged that the U.S.
measures are inconsistent with

03:38.033 --> 03:40.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the 2016 nuclear deal.

03:40.233 --> 03:42.666 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
And he warned of
reciprocal acts.

03:42.666 --> 03:45.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HASSAN ROUHANI, Iranian
President (through
translator): If Americans
pass new sanctions

03:45.966 --> 03:50.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in any form, or under
any pretext in Congress
or elsewhere, the great
nation of Iran will

03:50.666 --> 03:52.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have an appropriate answer.

03:52.733 --> 03:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We won't ignore violations
by the United States, and
will stand up to them.

03:56.033 --> 04:00.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also, the head
of the hard-line Revolutionary
Guards warned that the U.S.

04:00.966 --> 04:05.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had better pull its military
forces back at least 1,000
kilometers, or 600 miles, from

04:07.900 --> 04:09.800 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Iran.

04:09.800 --> 04:14.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. Supreme Court has
issued a split ruling on
enforcing the president's travel

04:14.800 --> 04:16.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ban.

04:16.766 --> 04:20.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The court today allowed the
administration to strictly
enforce a ban on refugees while

04:21.433 --> 04:23.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
an appeal moves
through lower courts.

04:23.566 --> 04:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the justices expanded the
list of people from six mostly
Muslim nations who are allowed

04:29.000 --> 04:31.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to visit the U.S.

04:31.366 --> 04:36.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back in this country, the
Justice Department is restoring
authority to local police to

04:38.000 --> 04:41.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
seize money and property
on suspicion they come
from criminal activity.

04:41.166 --> 04:45.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The assets can be taken
even without criminal
charges being brought.

04:45.433 --> 04:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Obama administration
had curbed the practice,
but Attorney General
Jeff Sessions today eased

04:51.166 --> 04:53.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the restrictions.

04:53.200 --> 04:57.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Wall Street, tech and health
care stocks fueled a day of
record highs across the board.

04:58.900 --> 05:03.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The Dow Jones industrial
average gained 66 points
to close at 21640.

05:04.400 --> 05:08.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Nasdaq rose 40, and
the S&amp;P 500 added 13.

05:08.466 --> 05:13.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Salem, Massachusetts,
today marked 325 years since
five women were hanged in the

05:16.133 --> 05:18.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
infamous witch trials.

05:18.266 --> 05:23.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They were among 19 people
condemned and hanged for
witchcraft in Salem in 1692.

05:25.266 --> 05:30.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A descendant of one of them
said it brings justice to the
fact that they were wrongly

05:30.666 --> 05:32.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
accused.

05:32.700 --> 05:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
two Republican senators on
their party's efforts to repeal

05:38.733 --> 05:41.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Obamacare; the president's
response to revelations
of his second conversation
with Vladimir Putin;

05:43.766 --> 05:48.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
two state views on the
controversial voter fraud
commission; and much more.

06:00.466 --> 06:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now we return to the battle
over health care and President
Trump's meeting with Senate

06:05.033 --> 06:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Republicans at the White House.

06:07.200 --> 06:11.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We hear from two people
who were in the room, first
Senator Pat Roberts of Kansas.

06:11.500 --> 06:15.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He is a member of the
Health, Education, Labor
and Pensions Committee.

06:15.933 --> 06:20.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I spoke with him a short time
ago and started by asking what
the president changed today

06:20.666 --> 06:22.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in his pitch to senators.

06:22.166 --> 06:24.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:24.200 --> 06:26.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAT ROBERTS (R), Kansas: We
had a meeting that I thought
was highly productive.

06:26.200 --> 06:30.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I thought the president made
a very good case that if you
simply have a repeal and, in two

06:32.333 --> 06:37.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
years, you're going to see
further deterioration, if that's
the right word, for Obamacare.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
In Kansas, our premiums
continue to soar.

06:43.100 --> 06:45.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're up now $3,000.

06:45.166 --> 06:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a little like being in
the back seat of a convertible
with Thelma and Louise and

06:51.000 --> 06:51.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we're headed toward the canyon.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're about at the edge.

06:53.133 --> 06:54.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we have got to do something.

06:54.366 --> 06:56.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Number one, we have
to get out of the car.

06:56.866 --> 06:59.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Number two, we have got
to get into a new car.

06:59.300 --> 07:01.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what the
president was talking about.

07:01.866 --> 07:03.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We had the entire
Republican Conference.

07:03.866 --> 07:05.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think he did a good message.

07:05.100 --> 07:09.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There was a good -- I
think he did a good job.

07:09.300 --> 07:12.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But what
has changed with your
Republican colleagues?

07:12.533 --> 07:15.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because, yesterday,
there weren't going to be
enough votes to do this.

07:15.900 --> 07:17.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Today, there are?

07:17.433 --> 07:19.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is that simply because of an
argument the president made?

07:19.200 --> 07:21.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:21.233 --> 07:23.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAT ROBERTS: Well, the first
thing is, Judy, is that we have
got to get over this business

07:23.900 --> 07:28.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of denying the leadership of
our party, Mitch McConnell,
at least a motion to proceed.

07:30.266 --> 07:32.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think the American people
want us to debate it.

07:32.300 --> 07:37.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think the American
people want us to vote
on several different
items that people would

07:37.700 --> 07:38.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be presenting.

07:38.633 --> 07:40.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is a vote-a-rama anyway.

07:40.333 --> 07:43.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You're probably going
to have 150 votes,.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But we need a debate
and we need to vote.

07:45.000 --> 07:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, this business of
stopping the motion to
proceed, that has to quit.

07:48.900 --> 07:52.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And that was one of the
main messages that the
president indicated,
to give Mitch McConnell

07:52.966 --> 07:57.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the -- obviously, the number
of votes he needed to go ahead
with this kind of an exercise.

07:59.066 --> 08:01.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think the president
really listened.

08:01.400 --> 08:06.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had at least 35 people,
maybe 40, make suggestions
with regards to the bill.

08:07.266 --> 08:08.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There was a lot of consensus.

08:08.066 --> 08:08.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

08:08.600 --> 08:10.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:10.533 --> 08:12.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAT ROBERTS: And the other thing
-- and I think he mentioned
this is much larger than

08:12.766 --> 08:17.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
health care -- is whether or not
Republicans can actually govern.

08:17.400 --> 08:19.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, you're
saying -- let me just clarify.

08:19.666 --> 08:24.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you're saying whether
Republicans can get together
as a group is more important

08:25.533 --> 08:26.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
than health care legislation?

08:26.800 --> 08:28.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:28.033 --> 08:30.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAT ROBERTS: No, it's
not more important.

08:30.033 --> 08:33.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's another consideration,
that, if we can't do this, maybe
you can't do tax reform or,

08:35.266 --> 08:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for that matter, anything
else on the table.

08:36.533 --> 08:37.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Both are very important.

08:37.800 --> 08:40.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Obviously, you have to
get health care right.

08:40.033 --> 08:42.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That was the whole
intent of the meeting.

08:42.500 --> 08:43.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He listened very carefully.

08:43.933 --> 08:46.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He stated his position
very forcefully.

08:46.600 --> 08:48.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I think it was
a good meeting.

08:48.633 --> 08:52.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let me
ask you about the fact that the
criticisms of this legislation

08:52.566 --> 08:54.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are the same today as
they were yesterday.

08:54.833 --> 08:57.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I'm just looking
at the state of Kansas.

08:57.266 --> 09:02.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Your hospital association had
-- had looked at the changes
you had proposed directing

09:03.133 --> 09:05.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
more money to the hospitals.

09:05.166 --> 09:08.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they said, that's great,
but they said, even with that,
it doesn't make up for the

09:08.366 --> 09:11.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
deep cuts to Medicaid and
other problems with the bill.

09:11.833 --> 09:14.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What would you say today to
your hospital association?

09:14.066 --> 09:16.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

09:16.200 --> 09:17.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAT ROBERTS: Well, as a matter
of fact, I'm meeting with them
just as I get through talking

09:17.566 --> 09:19.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with you.

09:19.233 --> 09:23.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I will point out to
them that Obamacare will
continue to deteriorate.

09:23.000 --> 09:28.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We have already lost
one insurance company;
42,000 Kansans don't
have insurance anymore.

09:29.900 --> 09:34.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if we lose our remaining
insurer, we're really
going to be in trouble.

09:36.300 --> 09:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it isn't so much what we
would like to have as what
is happening to Obamacare.

09:39.933 --> 09:44.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, working with the
Kansas Hospital Association,
I think there are going
to be some new ideas

09:46.566 --> 09:49.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
presented in whatever
bill that comes up with
- - or we come up with.

09:49.333 --> 09:52.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the president was
doing a lot of listening.

09:52.200 --> 09:57.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The White House was doing a lot
of listening, Tom Price, Seema
Verma, all the people within

09:58.800 --> 10:00.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the administration, that
they're going to come
up with something new.

